HEADWORD: Catenation
<hw>Cat`e*na"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>catenatio</ets>.]</ety> <def>Connection of links or union of parts,
as in a chain; a regular or connected series. See
<er>Concatenation</er>.</def> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catenulate</ent>⟦br⟧
